---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="CV">

  <section class="relative bg-gray-950 border-b border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/blueprint-hero-bg.png"
      alt=""
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-left-top opacity-40"
    />
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 text-center">
      <p class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-8">
        Career &amp; Service Record
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-[1.15] tracking-tight mb-8 text-white">
        Curriculum Vitae
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Ph.D., Business Analytics &amp; Data Science &middot; 25+ years federal civil service &middot; 35+ years fire service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-gray-500 mb-4">Education</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-white">Ph.D., Business Analytics and Data Science</p>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Capital Technology University · Laurel, MD · 2026</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1 italic">Dissertation: "Enhancing Data Accessibility and Quality Through Advanced Data Processing Techniques: A Case Study"</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-white">M.S., Geographical Information Systems</p>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Pennsylvania State University · 2011</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1 italic">Capstone: "Crowdsourcing Aquatic Resource Data Collection: Exploring Effective Methods to Collect and Rectify Citizen-Contributed Data" · American Geophysical Union Fall Meeting, 2011</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-white">B.S., Agronomy and Environmental Science</p>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Delaware Valley University · 1998</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-white">Graduate Studies, Environmental Management</p>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">University of Florida · 2003–2005</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 border-t border-gray-800 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-gray-500 mb-4">Federal Career</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Chief, Programs Integration Division, National Programs Branch</p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm whitespace-nowrap">2013–Present</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-3">U.S. Federal Government · Washington, DC</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">Directs national program and project management strategy for the largest civil engineering organization in the federal government. Oversees 25,000+ active projects globally representing trillions in infrastructure assets. Principal advisor to senior federal executives and the Office of Management and Budget on multi-billion-dollar annual appropriations.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Leading the complete replacement of <strong class="text-gray-300">PROMIS</strong>, USACE's largest and fully integrated program and project management AIS and the enterprise's primary automated information system, with a cloud-based, spatially enabled Oracle APEX platform; the single largest multifaceted system change in USACE history, target: mid-2027</li>
            <li>Oversees a portfolio of 40+ lessons and courses covering the full scope of USACE program and project management, delivered across 38 Districts and 8 Divisions</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="mt-4 border-l-2 border-blue-500 bg-blue-950/20 rounded-r-lg pl-4 pr-4 py-3">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-400 tracking-wide uppercase mb-1">Crisis Response</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
              Stood up a full emergency information system within 24 hours of a system blackout — then trained
              600+ users in under 60 days, at one-quarter the projected cost.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Special Assignment: Program Lead, Civil Works Business Intelligence and Geospatial Systems</p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm whitespace-nowrap">2020</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-3">USACE Institute for Water Resources · Alexandria, VA · GS-15 (Dual-hatted, concurrent with HQ role)</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">Competitively selected for a dedicated special assignment to modernize and spatially enable CWBI, USACE's primary Civil Works operations and maintenance AIS, while retaining full HQ responsibilities. Led CWBI across its full portfolio of 125+ modules and databases spanning navigation, regulatory, flood risk management, hydropower, natural resource management, and climate resilience; managed $20M in program resources.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Architected the spatial enablement of CWBI, the defining modernization of the system; integrated Civil Works operational data into a geospatially aware enterprise platform with global reach, bringing real-time spatial context to 200+ locks and dams and live multi-agency feeds from EPA, U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service, U.S. Coast Guard, and USDA</li>
            <li>Held concurrent oversight of the Civil Works geospatial system, the spatial data platform underpinning USACE's navigation, flood risk, dam safety, and environmental restoration missions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Nationwide Program Manager, Civil Works Construction, CAP &amp; Trust Fund Programs</p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm whitespace-nowrap">2012–2013</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-3">U.S. Federal Government · Washington, DC</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">National program management authority for Civil Works Construction, Continuing Authorities, and Trust Fund programs, collectively representing $3–5 billion in annual appropriations across navigation, flood risk management, dam safety, and ecosystem restoration.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Led the ground-up replacement of legacy Oracle tools with Oracle APEX for the enterprise Civil Works budget and appropriations tracking AIS, spatially enabled from inception; the system built in this role remains in full operation today</li>
            <li>The AIS produced the final President's Budget for Civil Works and managed the downstream allocation of Congressional appropriations across all Civil Works business lines</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Senior National Program Manager, Civil Works Regulatory Program</p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm whitespace-nowrap">2006–2012</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-3">U.S. Federal Government · Washington, DC</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">Led the national Regulatory Program across 8 Divisions and 36 Districts, $215M+ in appropriations, enabling $220B+ in annual economic development.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-400 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Delivered a 4th-generation national regulatory permit and mitigation management information system ($5M+ immediate savings, $1M+/year sustained)</li>
            <li>Co-authored the FGDC <em>National Wetland Mapping Standards</em>, the governing federal standard for wetland data nationwide</li>
            <li>Represented the Department of the Army at the International FOSS4G Conference, Sydney, Australia</li>
            <li class="text-blue-400 font-medium">EPA Partner of the Year (2009)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between gap-1 mb-2">
            <p class="font-semibold text-white">Chief, Regulatory Branch / Program Manager / Project Manager</p>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm whitespace-nowrap">2001–2008</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-3">U.S. Federal Government · Charleston, SC / Washington, DC / Jacksonville, FL</p>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">Competitively selected for national detail to redesign the federal government's environmental permit and mitigation tracking platform. Pioneered watershed-based cumulative impact assessment methodology adopted statewide by Florida DOT. As Branch Chief, advanced divisional ranking from bottom tier to top third in one year.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-400 font-medium mt-2">Commander's Award for Civilian Service (2005) · Superior Civilian Service Award (2008)</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="fire" class="mb-10 border-t border-gray-800 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-gray-500 mb-4">Emergency &amp; Fire Services</h2>
      <p class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">35+ Years · Active</p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">Three-plus decades of operational service in the fire service spanning front-line firefighting through organizational leadership. Certified at the national level across multiple disciplines; currently serving on a fire service Board of Directors.</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-400 list-disc list-inside mb-6">
        <li><span class="font-medium text-gray-300">Firefighter</span>, National Firefighter I &amp; II</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-gray-300">Fire Officer</span>, National Fire Officer I &amp; II</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-gray-300">Emergency Services Instructor</span>, I &amp; II</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-gray-300">Hazmat Technician</span></li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-gray-300">Board of Directors</span>, [Fire/EMS Organization]</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-gray-500 mb-2">Professional Certifications, Fire &amp; Emergency Services</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">To be added</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 border-t border-gray-800 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-gray-500 mb-4">Technical Skills</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-1">Data Science &amp; Engineering</p>
          <p>Python (pandas, NumPy, scikit-learn) · SQL · XML/USLM parsing · ETL pipelines · Data quality frameworks</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-1">Geospatial</p>
          <p>ArcGIS Enterprise &amp; Pro · QGIS · PostGIS · GeoPandas · cartopy · matplotlib · Jupyter spatial notebooks · Federal wetland data standards · Oracle APEX spatial enablement</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-1">Application Development</p>
          <p>Oracle APEX · Cloud infrastructure · JavaScript/HTML/CSS · Git/GitHub</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-1">Databases</p>
          <p>Oracle · PostgreSQL · SQLite</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10 border-t border-gray-800 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-gray-500 mb-4">Awards &amp; Recognition</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-400 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Commander's Award for Civilian Service (×2)</li>
        <li>Superior Civilian Service Award</li>
        <li>EPA Partner of the Year (2009)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>
